name: Des Plaines Trail System
description: Follows the Des Plaines River for 22 miles in Cook County and another 31 miles north through Lake County.

name: Tinley Creek Trail System
description:
Four paved loops take visitors over gently rolling hills, through prairies and forests, and alongside wetlands
and ravines.

name: Horizon Farm Trails
Salt Creek Trail System
description: Features a long paved trail from Brookfield Woods (outside Brookfield Zoo) to Bemis Woods.

name: Major Taylor Trail
description: Connects to the paved loop trail at Dan Ryan Woods and continues for about 7 miles southeast, eventually connecting to the Cal-Sag Trail.

name: Busse Forest Trails
description: Large paved loop circling Busse Reservoir with shorter trail segments fanning out from the loop.

name: Plum Creek Trail
Burnham Prairie Trail
Palos Trail System
description: An extensive and vaired trail system winding through the 15,000 acre Palos Preserves.

name: Thorn Creek Trail System
description: Connects multiple forest preserves, winding past lakes and wetlands, and through woodlands abundant with birds and other wildlife.

name: Calumet Trail System
Kickapoo Woods Trail
Orland Grassland Trail System
description: Perimeter loop trail provides a buffer from Orland Grassland's valuable natural areas, while showcasing the significant restoration work that has taken place there.

name: Deer Grove Trails
description: Vast, looping trail system makes it easy to access the preserve's diverse habitats and creates ample space for extended runs or hikes.

name: Burnham Greenway Trail
description: Former railroad right-of-way linking Chicago to Lansing.

name: Cal-Sag Trail
description: Links the Centennial and I&M Canal trails in the west to Freedom Park in Alsip in the east. By 2017, will extend east to the Burnham Greenway and Chicago Lakefront trails.

name: North Branch Trail System
description: Winds along the North Branch of the Chicago River and Skokie Lagoons, providing access to various preserves, golf courses and the Chicago Botanic Garden.

name: Centennial Trail
description: Located within the I&M Canal National Heritage Corridor, the first national park of its kind. Provides a connection to the Cal-Sag Trail.

name: Volmer Road Grove Loop
John Husar I&M Canal Trail
description: Located within the I&M Canal National Heritage Corridor, the first national park of its kind. Provides a connection to the Cal-Sag Trail.

name: Paul Douglas Trail
description: Paved loop trail with a connection to the Crabtree Trail and Crabtree Nature Center.

name: Spring Lake Trails
Miller Meadow Trail
Poplar Creek Trail System
description: Large paved loop circling the eastern portion of the Poplar Creek Preserves intersects with looped unpaved trails in the western portion.

name: Perkins Woods Trails
Dan Ryan Trails
Sag Valley Trail System
description: Miles of looping and connecting unpaved trails take visitors to some of the most remote areas of Cook County.

name: Oak Forest Heritage Preserve Trails
description: Loop trail following the rolling topography of the Oak Forest Heritage Preserve, highlighting the historically and ecologically significant areas.

name: Midlothian Meadows Trails
Arie Crown Trails
description: Offers riders a natural setting of gently rolling hills and breathtaking beauty as it winds through the woods.

name: Crabtree Trail
description: Paved trail runs southeast from the Old Stover Road Trailhead (across from Crabtree Nature Center) to the Paul Douglas Trail.
